{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 09:24:02.301605", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.219)\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_incorrect_ip\"]\n\nRationale:\n- The diagnosis found an administrative IP addressing inconsistency: host_2_1_1_1 configured with 10.2.1.219, which deviates from the expected addressing scheme and likely represents an out-of-range static IP assignment. While this did not cause reachability failures in the collected data, it is an administrative anomaly that can cause future operational issues, so I marked it as an anomaly and selected host_incorrect_ip as the root cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2166, "output_tokens": 149, "total_tokens": 2315, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
